26/01/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A former Bosnian Serb policeman wanted for war crimes surrendered to EUFOR on Tuesday (25 January).
Boban Simcic served as a guard at a prison camp in Visegrad where inmates were tortured and killed.
He gave himself up after months of negotiations with the Bosnian Serb police.
In other news, the Federation of BiH government confirmed Tuesday that it has provided guarantees for the temporary release on bail of indictee Pasko Ljubicic.
The Bosnian Croat, indicted for war crimes against Bosniak civilians in 1992 and 1993, turned himself in and has been in ICTY custody since 2001.
(AFP, PBS BiH, Pincom.info, NTV Hayat, Fena - 25/01/05)
